    "While the advancement of technology has brought about innovative feedback modalities such as audio or video (Munshi & Deneen, 2018; Payne et al., 2022), there are inherent challenges in ensuring their efficacy and succinctness, especially when the feedback providers are NESB teaching staff (Bal-Gezegin, 2015; Demir & Özmen, 2017).",
    "Notably, NESB educators may often grapple in providing feedback with language and sentence structure (Starfield, 2019).",
